<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO TANKER</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan  7 19:35:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dear Tanker,<br><br>
Thank you for your reply. One of my colleagues, Nguyen Hoang was a civilian living in Hue during the '68 Tet Offensive. He will speak to my class on January 30th along with three American veterans and an American medical support person. All these perspectives on Tet will be highly valued by my students.<br><br>
On the evening of February 13th, we will have several Vietnamese colleagues speak about leaving Viet Nam, the difficulties of coming to America, adjustment, and how they are doing. One speaker has just returned from a &quot;re-education camp,&quot; and his perspective is rather different.<br><br>
Please write again. I would appreciate if you would let other veterans in your geographical area know about this dialog string, so they might post their views and comments as well.<br><br>
Stay dry. The dikes to the east of our house are holding....at least it is not raining!<br><br>
Regards and best wishes,<br><br>
L. Grivetti<br>

